WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:01.470
<v Narrator>As always, it's good to see</v>

00:00:01.470 --> 00:00:04.050
what is the shared responsibility model for Amazon S3.

00:00:04.050 --> 00:00:05.950
So AWS is going to be responsible

00:00:05.950 --> 00:00:07.800
for all the infrastructure.

00:00:07.800 --> 00:00:10.200
That includes all the things specific to S3

00:00:10.200 --> 00:00:12.520
so that their ability, availability,

00:00:12.520 --> 00:00:14.290
the fact that it can actually sustain

00:00:14.290 --> 00:00:16.850
current losses of two facilities.

00:00:16.850 --> 00:00:19.990
As well as, I will see their own internal configuration

00:00:19.990 --> 00:00:21.980
and vulnerability analysis.

00:00:21.980 --> 00:00:23.630
And their own compliance validation

00:00:23.630 --> 00:00:25.800
internally within their infrastructure.

00:00:25.800 --> 00:00:27.960
And you as a user of Amazon S3,

00:00:27.960 --> 00:00:30.640
you're supposed to set up correctly S3 Versioning

00:00:30.640 --> 00:00:33.380
to make sure you set up the right S3 Bucket Policy

00:00:33.380 --> 00:00:36.150
so that the data is protected within your buckets.

00:00:36.150 --> 00:00:37.960
You need to make sure that if you want verification

00:00:37.960 --> 00:00:39.300
you set it up yourself.

00:00:39.300 --> 00:00:41.290
Logging and monitoring is optional

00:00:41.290 --> 00:00:43.240
so you have to enable it yourself.

00:00:43.240 --> 00:00:45.966
Making sure that you are using the most optimal

00:00:45.966 --> 00:00:48.890
cost storage cloud that is going to be

00:00:48.890 --> 00:00:51.690
the most cost friendly is also your responsibility.

00:00:51.690 --> 00:00:54.000
And finally, if you wanted to encrypt your data

00:00:54.000 --> 00:00:55.530
onto your Amazon S3 bucket,

00:00:55.530 --> 00:00:57.470
that is up to you as well, okay?

00:00:57.470 --> 00:00:59.350
So here we can really see what is the difference

00:00:59.350 --> 00:01:01.018
between the responsibility of

00:01:01.018 --> 00:01:05.180
AWS and yourself in this Amazon S3 service.

00:01:05.180 --> 00:01:06.030
All right, that's it.

00:01:06.030 --> 00:01:07.780
I will see you in the next lecture.